item.name: blocked clients
item.description: Number of clients pending on a blocking call (BLPOP, BRPOP, BRPOPLPUSH)

item.name: client biggest input buf
item.description: biggest input buffer among current client connections

item.name: client longest output list
item.description: longest output list among current client connections

item.name: connected clients
item.description: Number of client connections (excluding connections from slaves)

item.name: connected slaves
item.description: Number of connected slaves

item.name: evicted keys
item.description: Number of evicted keys due to maxmemory limit

item.name: expired keys
item.description: Total number of key expiration events

item.name: instantaneous operation count
item.description: Number of commands processed per second

item.name: keyspace hits
item.description: Number of successful lookup of keys in the main dictionary

item.name: keyspace misses
item.description: Number of failed lookup of keys in the main dictionary

item.name: latest fork msec
item.description: Duration of the latest fork operation in microseconds (convert to msec)

item.name: loading
item.description: Flag indicating if the load of a dump file is on-going

item.name: memory fragmentation ratio
item.description: Ratio between used_memory_rss and used_memory

item.name: rdb bgsave in progress
item.description: Flag indicating a RDB save is on-going

item.name: rdb changes since last save
item.description: Number of changes since the last dump

item.name: rdb last bgsave time sec
item.description: Duration of the last RDB save operation in seconds

item.name: version
item.description: Version of the Redis server

item.name: rejected connections
item.description: Number of connections rejected because of maxclients limit

item.name: role
item.description: Value is "master" if the instance is slave of no one, or "slave" if the instance is enslaved to a master. Note that a slave can be master of another slave (daisy chaining).

item.name: commands processed
item.description: Total number of commands processed by the server

item.name: connections received
item.description: Total number of connections accepted by the server

item.name: used memory
item.description: Total number of bytes allocated by Redis using its allocator

item.name: used memory lua
item.description: Number of bytes used by the Lua engine

item.name: used memory rss
item.description: Number of bytes that Redis allocated as seen by the operating system (a.k.a resident set size). This is the number reported by tools such as top(1) and ps(1)

Redis rdb last bgsave time in second
